        public void addProduct​(EPSProduct product)
        Add to the List of EPSProduct items in the transaction.

        A list of products is only required if payment cards with restricted use (e.g. fuels cards) are to be supported.

        The list shows which items can be or have been accepted by the terminal or payment system (implementation dependent)

      • getAcquirerTransactionReference

        public String getAcquirerTransactionReference()
        Get the Sequence or other identifying number/text allocated by the core implementation or acquirer for this transaction.

        Normally this would be a number, also referred to as STAN (System Trace Audit Number), but it can be a string.

        This should be a unique value, which can be used for tracking and may be required for any subsequent attempt to reverse the transaction, or to link pre-auth and final details.

        Returns:
        acquirerTransactionReference

      • getBaseTender

        public EPSTender getBaseTender()
        Get the Total amount/value tendered.

        If the tender is not made in the base currency, this property should be set to the base currency value of the tendered amount. The foreign currency tender should be set in setDCCTender(EPSTender)

        The tendered amount may be different from the requested amount if, for example cashback were added, or a part payment were made. The tendered amount can be set in one two ways: 

           1. Explicitly by calling setTender(java.math.BigDecimal) or setBaseTender(manito.eft.interfaces.EPSTender)
   2. Implicitly by omission - the tendered amount will be assumed to match the requested amount.

        The tendered amount can be set negative to indicate that goods or services have been added rather than any payment being taken. e.g online top-up.

        Returns:
        baseTender

      • getErrorCode

        public int getErrorCode()
        Get the Error code.

        Whilst this does allow a range of error conditions, it should be noted that the POS may only recognise SUCCESS or FAILURE, as indeed is the case with Lucas.

        The preferred method is to report the error condition as text in the OperatorMessage and just use the setSuccessful() method, which sets the error code to either SUCCESS or FAILURE. 

          Error Codes:
   E_SUCCESS                    Action successful in its entirety
   E_PARTIAL_FAILURE            Action only partially successful, other parts may need reversal
   E_FAILURE                    Failure - unspecified reason
   E_DEVICE_UNAVAILABLE         Failure - requested device unavailable
   E_BUSY                       Failure - system busy
   E_LOGGED_OUT                 Failure - logon required
   E_ABORTED                    Failure - aborted by operator
   E_TIMED_OUT                  Failure - timeout
   E_FORMAT_ERROR               Failure - Format Error
   E_PARSING_ERROR              Failure - Parsing error
   E_COMMUNICATION_ERROR        Failure - Communications error
   E_VALIDATION_ERROR           Failure - XML Validation error
   E_MISSING_MANDATORY_DATA     Failure - Missing data
   E_UNKNOWN_CARD               Failure - Unknown Card
        Returns:
        errorCode

      • getLoyaltyAutoRedemptionType

        public int getLoyaltyAutoRedemptionType()
        Get the Code showing how the LoyaltyAutoRedemptionValue is to be applied. 
          Codes:

      • getTender

        public BigDecimal getTender()
        Get the Total amount/value tendered.

        If the tender is not made in the base currency, this property should be set to the base currency value of the tendered amount. The foreign currency tender should be set in setDCCTender(EPSTender)

        The tendered amount may be different from the requested amount if, for example cashback were added, or a part payment were made. The tendered amount can be set in one two ways: 

           1. Explicitly by calling setTender(java.math.BigDecimal) or setBaseTender(manito.eft.interfaces.EPSTender)
   2. Implicitly by omission - the tendered amount will be assumed to match the requested amount.

        The tendered amount can be set negative to indicate that goods or services have been added rather than any payment being taken. e.g online top-up.

        Returns:
        baseTender.getValue()

      • setErrorCode

        public void setErrorCode​(int errorCode)
        Set the Error code.

        Whilst this does allow a range of error conditions, it should be noted that the POS may only recognise SUCCESS or FAILURE, as indeed is the case with Lucas.

        The preferred method is to report the error condition as text in the OperatorMessage and just use the setSuccessful() method, which sets the error code to either SUCCESS or FAILURE. 

          Error Codes:
   E_SUCCESS                    Action successful in its entirety
   E_PARTIAL_FAILURE            Action only partially successful, other parts may need reversal
   E_FAILURE                    Failure - unspecified reason
   E_DEVICE_UNAVAILABLE         Failure - requested device unavailable
   E_BUSY                       Failure - system busy
   E_LOGGED_OUT                 Failure - logon required
   E_ABORTED                    Failure - aborted by operator
   E_TIMED_OUT                  Failure - timeout
   E_FORMAT_ERROR               Failure - Format Error
   E_PARSING_ERROR              Failure - Parsing error
   E_COMMUNICATION_ERROR        Failure - Communications error
   E_VALIDATION_ERROR           Failure - XML Validation error
   E_MISSING_MANDATORY_DATA     Failure - Missing data
   E_UNKNOWN_CARD               Failure - Unknown Card
        Parameters:
        errorCode - the errorCode
